result.execSummary:
The defendant Cody Lee Frambs was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Battery, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Credit for 6 days only if revoked.

miscConds.notes:
The defendant must obtain his HS diploma or equivalent.

The defendant must maintain/obtain full time employment/school that consists of at least 35 hrs/week.

When not full time employed/school, the defendant must apply for at least 3 jobs per week and report progress monthly to P&P with pertinent information in regards to applications.  The defendant must only apply for jobs qualified for - must accept any job offered - must not engage in any conduct that could result in the termination of his/her employment/school.

The defendant may not have contact with the victim.

The defendant must not possess or consume alcohol and no entry into any taverns or bars.

The defendant must participate and complete an anger managment program and follow thru with any recommendations.

The defendant must submit to a psychological evaluation and follow thru with any recommendations and/or treatment plans.

The defendant must take all medications as prescribed by a medical provider or physician and in the manner in which they are prescribed.
The defendant must undergo an AODA assessment and follow thru with all recommendations.

Same conditions as count #1 except no additional community service or restitution.

records.addlTxt: Called at 9:13 AM. Cody Frambs appears in person and with counsel Thomas Roley. State appears by Charles Simono. State - have complied with victim notification requirements and they are in the courtroom today. State -  joint recommendation of 2 years probation with conditions of: court costs on each count, anger management, psychological screen/assessment and follow thru, AODA and follow thru, restitution for a medical bill of $1590.35 plus $159.03 in VW surchage totalling $1749.38. Victim now states that this bill was paid by insurance, only costs are out-of-pocket expenses for missed work - verbal requests for missed work and mileage totalling approximately $80.00. Court reviews restitution request and those requests are on the report totalling $78.58. Defendant does not object to the restitution amount/request. State continues with comments, victims family would like to make statement. Roley - follow joint recommendation. - asks for 6 days credit if revoked. Frambs withholds comment. Victim makes statement (parents). Defendant makes statement, remorseful. Court sentences the defendant to the following: counts #1 and #3 - withhold sentence and place on probation for 2 years, concurrent to each other, with conditions of: AODA and follow thru, costs - paid thru probation, participate and complete anger management and follow thru, submit to psychological evaluation and follow up with all recommendations and/or treatment plans, pay restitution of $86.43 - paid thru probation, no consumption or possession of alcohol and no entry into any bars or tavners, obtain HSED or equiavleient, take all meds as prescribed by treating physician or medical provider and in the manner in which they are prescribed, no contact with victim, 150 hours of community service, maintain/obtain full time employment/school, credit for 6 days only if revoked, right to appeal, adjourned.
Sentencing hearing on September 22, 2014 at 09:00 am.

Called at 4:51 PM. Cody Frambs appears in person and with counsel Thomas Roley. State appears by Charles Simono.  State - this is a plea hearing only as vicitms have not been notified and they want to be present - amend count #1 to mids battery contrary to 940.19(1) and defendant will plead G to amended count #1, #2 - DRI, #3 - amend to misd battery 940.19(1) and then plead G, joint recommendation of 2 years probation with court costs on each count, AODA and follow thru, anger management and follow thru, psychological evalation/assessment and follow thru, restitition of approximately $1300.00, absolute sobriety, no alcohol, continue education and obtain HS diploma, take any and all medications as prescribed by treating physician or medical provbider, no contact with victim. State cannot proceed to sentencing today due to notification of victims and defendant and Roley understand that. Court amends counts #1 and #3 to misd battery contrary to 940.19(1) - reads new charges and penalties, court dismisses and reads in count #2. Frambs plead G to both amended count #1 and amended count #3. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his constitutional rights by entering his plea and right to JT, accepts plea, continues bond, set for sentencing hearing on 9/22/14 at 9:00 AM.
Jury trial on September 22, 2014 at 08:30 am.

Called at 2:34 PM. Cody Frambs appears in person and with counsel Thomas Roley. State appears by Charles Simono. Roley - has received agreement, not accepting agreement, requests JT. Court continues bond, set for JT on 9/22/14 at 8:30 AM.
Final pre-trial on August 20, 2014 at 01:15 pm.

Called at 3:18 PM. Cody Frambs appears in person and with counsel Thomas Roley. State appears by JBC. State calls Chief Michael Ashbeck. Ashbeck sworn in at 3:19 PM. Direct exam by State. Record reflects proper identification of the defendant. Cross exam by Roley at 3:27 PM. State objects - relevance - sustained (3:28 PM). State objects - relevance - sustained (3:30 PM). Court finds probable cause that a felony was committed, binds over for trial. State files Information that mirrors complaint. Roley has Information, waives reading of it, enters NG pleas to all counts. Court accepts pleas, continues bond, set for FPT on 8/20/14 at 1:15 PM.
